The paper focuses on learning binary visual representations using deep networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of binary representations in image retrieval (cs.IR) and object detection (cs.MM), which are both relevant sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a new method for learning binary representations, which could be considered a contribution to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
